content:
Exactly. You need to make sure you're in the correct repository directory before proceeding.

Run this first to get back to the main repository directory:

```bash
cd ~/github/palios-taey-nova
```

Then verify your remote is set correctly:

```bash
git remote -v
```

- If you **don't see** any remotes listed, add it:

```bash
git remote add origin git@github.com:palios-taey/palios-taey-nova.git
```

Then force push again (assuming you're on your `main` branch):

```bash
git push origin main --force
```

That's the safest, cleanest way forward. Let me know how it goes!
